2. For EU or EEA nationals moving to Germany after August 2019, additional requirements apply. From the fourth month after entry, the requirements of the Freedom of Movement Act must be met. EU/EEA nationals have freedom of movement if they 
   2.1 Are self-employed or employed (GREEN)
   2.2 Are seeking work or involuntarily unemployed (GREEN)
   2.3 Can derive their freedom of movement from a family member (YELLOW: depends on the family member's status)
   2.4 Have sufficient means of subsistence and sufficient health insurance coverage, or (YELLOW: meaning of sufficient means of subsistence and sufficient health insurance coverage must be inferred or explained)
   2.5 Have acquired a permanent right of residence. (GREEN)
3. Parents are not EU, EEA or Swiss citizens but have a valid residence permit or a specific residence title that entitles them to work, or (GREEN)
4. Parents are recognized refugees or entitled to asylum. (GREEN)
5. The child must have its residence or usual place of residence in Germany or in another EU, EEA or Swiss state. (GREEN)

